init_text: When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We watched as we grew up, got married, had kids, and then died.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We watched as our bodies were buried, and we watched as our souls were sent to the cinema.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We watched as we were reincarnated into a new life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I was born in a small town in the middle of nowhere.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: My parents were poor, and I was the youngest of three children.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I had a sister who was five years older than me, and a brother who was seven years older than me.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I had a normal childhood, and I had a normal life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I went to school, I did my homework, and I had friends.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I was a happy kid, but I was also a lonely kid.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I had no friends at school, and I had no friends at home.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I had no one to talk to, and I had no one to play with.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I was alone, and I was always alone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I was happy with my life, and I was happy with my family.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were each others first love and first kiss.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were happy and we were a happy family.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were happy, we were content, and we were living the American dream.
